    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>SETTLEMENT AT BOMBARDIER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Tentative agreement is reached between Bombardier and 3,800 striking production and office workers at its Montreal aerospace unit; plant has been idle since June 22; union says three-year contract provides 2 percent wage increases in each year (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A tentative agreement was reached over the weekend between Bombardier, the aircraft and rail-car maker based in Montreal, and 3,800 striking production and office workers at its Toronto aerospace unit. The plant had been idle since last Thursday. The union said the three-year contract provides 2 percent wage increases in each year.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard (NYT)</p>
      </block>
